<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: TROUT ARE BIG STORY AS TOURNAMENT NEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If fishing remains as good as it has been in recent weeks, this year's May 
Trout Classic, Saturday and Sunday at Big Bear Lake, could be one of the most 
memorable. 
</P>
<P>
 All the marinas are weighing in limits, but it is the size of the fish that 
has everyone's attention. Al D'Emanuele of Fawnskin, Calif., used a glob of red 
and green Power Bait to lure an eight-pound trout, and Gordon Griffith of 
Lancaster used a Rapala lure to catch a 7-pound 4-ounce fish. 
</P>
<P>
 "Looks like we've got the lake primed for the tournament," Griffith said. The 
tournament, limited to 400 entries, is sold out. 
</P>
