<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; PARQUE FITS CRESCENTA VALLEY FOR TIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Parque pitched a five-hitter and struck out 15 as Crescenta Valley High 
defeated Hoover, 10-2, Tuesday in a Pacific League game, clinching a tie for 
its first baseball title since 1980. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons (15-5, 12-2 in league play) can win the title outright by beating 
Glendale on Thursday. Parque (10-2), a left-handed senior, pitched his seventh 
complete game. Kirk Hagge and John French each had two hits and drove in two 
runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Rio Mesa 5, Santa Barbara 4 -- Rio Mesa (18-5, 11-2) clinched the Channel 
League championship, its fourth in five years and seventh in 10. Steve Arneson 
drove in two runs with a single in the fourth and Vince Roman drove in the 
decisive run with a double in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale 6, Quartz Hill 2 -- David Glick (9-2) pitched a seven-hitter -- his 
eighth complete game of the season -- and struck out seven for host Palmdale 
(17-6, 10-4) in the Golden League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 12, Granada Hills 3 -- Kenny Bernas had a double, triple and three 
RBIs for Kennedy (12-9, 7-6) in a North Valley League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus 11, Burbank 2 -- Brandon Hernandez pitched five shutout innings for the 
Centurions (15-7-1, 7-4) in a Foothill League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 4, Oxnard 4 -- Ventura left 17 runners on base and Oxnard stranded 12 
in a Channel league game called after 12 innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 10, Burroughs Ridgecrest 9 -- Derrick Ford and James Juneau 
hit run-scoring singles with two out in the seventh to give the Antelopes 
(10-9, 9-4) a Golden League victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Hueneme 14, Dos Pueblos 11 -- Mike Bush capped a six-run fifth inning with a 
three-run triple, putting Hueneme (11-14, 5-8) ahead in a Channel League game. 
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar 2, Kennedy 0 -- Cherise Espinosa (10-8) pitched a four-hitter for 
Sylmar (11-8) in a City Section 4-A Division quarterfinal. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real 1, Granada Hills 0 -- Jennifer Gould pitched a two-hitter and 
drove in the run in a City 4-A quarterfinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus 3, Burbank 2 -- Chris Gill's run-scoring single in the bottom of the 
seventh gave the Centurions (23-2-1, 10-0-1) a the Foothill League 
championship. BOYS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys d. Franklin, 15-5, 7-15, 15-12, 15-11 -- Bryan Oey made 16 kills and 
Ricardo Hernandez added 21 assists for host Van Nuys (15-2) in a City 3-A 
semifinal match. The Wolves will face Marshall in the final at 5:30 p.m. Friday 
at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
