<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARGARET SKEETE, 115; OLDEST AMERICAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Margaret Skeete, listed in the Guinness Book of World Records as the oldest 
American, died Saturday at her home. She was 115. 
</P>
<P>
 Mrs. Skeete had been bedridden since a fall three weeks ago and died in her 
sleep, said her daughter, Verne Taylor. 
</P>
<P>
 Guinness listed Mrs. Skeete for the first time in its 1993 edition, after 
verifying her age from an 1880 census that listed her as a 2-year-old, Mrs. 
Taylor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mrs. Skeete was born Oct. 27, 1878, in Rockport, Tex. When her husband died 41 
years ago, she moved from Texas to Virginia to live with Taylor's family. 
</P>
<P>
 She outlived two children. 
</P>
<P>
 Mrs. Skeete was unimpressed by her longevity. "I guess that's something, but 
it doesn't buy me anything," she said at her 115th birthday party in October. 
Her daughter said she maintained a craving for sweets until a few weeks ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
