<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; CHURCH TO EXHIBIT AIDS MEMORIAL QUILT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By -- MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 St. Philip's Catholic Church is inviting the public to view the Names Project 
AIDS Memorial Quilt on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The quilt project began in 1987 when a small group of people sewed together 
square panels as a tribute to people who have died of AIDS. The quilt now has 
thousands of squares. 
</P>
<P>
 The all-day exhibit will be at the church, at the corner of Gilbert Street and 
Valencia Drive. No admission will be charged. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 871-3610. -- MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
