<P>
ALL-STAR SOFTBALL GAME ROSTERS ANNOUNCED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county's leading hitter, Alison Johnsen, leads some of the county's best 
seniors into the third Orange County North-South all-star softball game. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosters for the June 8 game, to played at 7 p.m. at Brea-Olinda High, were 
released Tuesday by the Soroptimist International of Brea, a women's business 
charitable organization sponsoring the game. 
</P>
<P>
 No more than two players are allowed from each school. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets can be obtained by calling (714) 990-7636. 
</P>
<P>
 The rosters: 
</P>
<P>
 North -- Amanda Adams, Cypress; Jamie Al-Moradi, Canyon; Kristi Bolle, El 
Modena; Laurie Fritz, Kennedy; Heather Hamer, El Dorado; Kristy Hensel, 
Kennedy; Dawn Kobata, Villa Park; Nina Lindenberg, Canyon; Julie Littman, 
Rancho Alamitos; Jill Otto, Rancho Alamitos; Chris Puccio, Orange; Christa 
Saindon, Cypress; Carolyn Wilson, Los Alamitos; Debbie Wilson, Los Alamitos; 
Nicola Walsh, Rosary. Coach: Lance Eddy, Canyon. Assistants: Jami Shannon, Los 
Alamitos; Ron Douglas, Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
 South -- Keri Byrd, Woodbridge; Sarah Davis, Tustin; Lise Delligatta, Santa 
Margarita; Patty Godwin, Mater Dei; Alison Johnsen, Woodbridge; Christy 
Journell, Laguna Hills; Carrie Kirk, University; Candace Kollen, Mater Dei; 
Misty Lauby, El Toro; Jodi Morris, Capistrano Valley; Stefanie Noffsinger, 
Huntington Beach; Janee Sansone, Ocean View; Alycia Stevens, Laguna Hills; 
Natalie Tomoguchi, Irvine; Racquel Willson, Ocean View. Coach: Alan Dugard, 
Woodbridge. Assistants: Jim Daugherty, El Toro; Mike Borowski, Santa Margarita. 
</P>
