<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Esa Sallinen 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Burroughs 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Track and field 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: The Finnish exchange student is undefeated in outdoor 
competition and has cleared 16 feet or higher in four straight meets. He capped 
that streak with a personal best of 16 feet 4 3/4 inches in last Wednesday's 
Foothill League finals. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Sallinen moved to fourth on the all-time region list -- and 
to second on the yearly state list -- with his personal best vault, yet 
Burroughs assistant Mike McHorney said he is capable of jumping substantially 
higher. "His technique in bending the pole is really starting to improve," 
McHorney said. "If he can keep that going until the state championships, he's 
got a chance to clear 17 feet." 
</P>
