<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Matthias Otte 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Swimming 
</P>
<P>
 Otte, from Marx High School in Rathenow, Germany, helped Orange Coast dominate 
the State swimming and diving championships last weekend.The Pirates had 521 
points and second-place Golden West had 417. Otte won the 200-yard individual 
medley (1:52.50) and the 100 butterfly (50.13). He also was part of OCC teams 
that won the 200- and 400-medley relays, and the 200 and 400 freestyle relays. 
Otte also finished second in the 200 backstroke and tied teammate Grant 
Ferguson for high-point total. He also was a member of the 1992 OCC team that 
won the State title. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Grant Ferguson of OCC won the 100 and the 200 breaststroke and was on four 
winning relay teams at the State swimming championships. 
</P>
