<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: EARLY HEARING COULD RETURN SCYPHERS TO FIELD LATER TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A hearing to determine whether Mike Scyphers can return to coaching is 
scheduled for 8:30 a.m. today at Ventura County Superior Court in Ventura, said 
Lawrence Trygstad, an attorney representing parents of Simi Valley High 
players. 
</P>
<P>
 The parents are seeking a temporary restraining order that would reinstate 
Scyphers, who has been suspended as Simi Valley High baseball coach pending a 
police and school district investigation into possible financial and 
disciplinary improprieties. 
</P>
<P>
 If Judge John J. Hunter rules in the parents' favor, Scyphers, 41, could be on 
the field for the Pioneers' game today at Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
 A group of parents who support Scyphers will meet with Supt. Mary Beth Wolford 
and Principal Kathryn Scroggin at 7:30 this morning at the Simi Valley Unified 
School District office. JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
