 RACER: The first injury during practice for the Indy 500 usually makes the 
news, and this year it has special interest in the Valley. . . . The injured 
racer, Mike Groff, graduated from Chatsworth High in 1979. Groff bruised his 
foot Monday when his engine blew and he slid into a wall. 
