 CREDIT DUE: There are two ways to get an increased credit line on your credit 
cards. You can call your card company and apply for it. Or you can do it 
yourself by electronically altering the magnetic stripe on the back. The second 
method avoids those troublesome credit checks, but it is, of course, illegal 
and could land you in jail. (B6) 
</P>
