<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY: MOORPARK; RESIDENTIAL TOXIC WASTE PICKUP SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Moorpark residents will be able to rid their homes of old paints, solvents, 
pesticides, cleansers and batteries from 9 a.m. to noon Saturday during the 
city's first collection of household hazardous waste. 
</P>
<P>
 A maximum of five gallons or 50 pounds of material will be accepted from each 
resident, said Jill Ruben-Myers, Moorpark's coordinator of solid waste.The city 
will not accept business or commercial waste, used medical supplies, old 
explosives, tires, or radioactive material, Ruben-Myers said.  
</P>
<P>
 Because waste space will be limited to that of 250 residents, appointments are 
required. Residents will be notified of the location of the collection site -- 
and provided with maps -- when they make appointments. 
</P>
<P>
 Appointments may be made using the city's 24-hour appointment line at 
529-6864, Ext. 333. The deadline for calling is 5 p.m. Thursday. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
