<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Defensive end Robert Young agreed to terms on a three-year, $3.5-million 
contract with the Rams and expects to sign in the next few days, said his 
agent, Steve Feldman. 
</P>
<P>
 Young, a restricted free agent, accepted the offer made Monday by the Rams.He 
earned the NFL-minimum $150,000 for a third-year player last season but will 
receive a substantial raise after emerging as one of the team's top pass 
rushers. 
</P>
<P>
 Young, 25, had seven sacks in the first four weeks of the season before 
injuring his knee against New Orleans and later undergoing arthroscopic knee 
surgery. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams also signed free-agent receiver Greg McMurtry to a one-year contract 
worth $500,000. McMurtry, 6 feet 2 and 210 pounds, caught 22 passes for 241 
yards and a touchdown last season for the New England Patriots. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
