<HEADLINE>
<P>
TARKANIAN TURNS DOWN AZTEC JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GENE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerry Tarkanian, former Nevada Las Vegas basketball coach, said Tuesday that 
he turned down the San Diego State job last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 "The program is down, but I think we could build it up," he said."That wasn't 
the problem. I was excited Saturday . . . but I just didn't feel it was the 
right time for me." 
</P>
<P>
 The Aztecs, who finished 12-16 overall (6-12 in the Western Athletic 
Conference), are in search of a replacement for Tony Fuller, who returned to 
his alma mater, Pepperdine, after two seasons at San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the possible successors: Tim Grgurich, a former UNLV assistant coach who 
is on the Seattle SuperSonics' staff. 
</P>
<P>
 Tarkanian said he wouldn't rule out the possibility of a return to college 
coaching. GENE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
