<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; NEW YORK; DIOXIN'S DANGER TO FETUS, IMMUNITY TOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Environmental Protection Agency scientists have concluded that the primary 
threats from dioxin are subtle effects on fetal development and the immune 
system that may come from very low exposure levels, a published report says. 
Most people have dioxin levels in their bodies at or close to the levels that 
cause immune system and fetal problems in lab animals, the scientists said in 
the draft summary of a 2,000-page report, which was described in the New York 
Times. But the report says that many of its conclusions came from animal 
studies. 
</P>
