<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A second adult mountain lion was killed by federal trackers in eastern San 
Diego County, about 10 miles south of where a female lion was killed earlier in 
the day. 
</P>
<P>
 The 125-pound male was killed about 10:45 p.m. Monday. The owner of a private 
Descanso ranch told officials that a 120-pound pregnant ewe on the ranch had 
been killed and partly eaten by a mountain lion Monday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier Monday, park rangers tracked and killed an adult female mountain lion 
in Cuyamaca Rancho State Park, a day after a big cat charged a child. 
