<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN DROPS RAPE CASE AGAINST DETECTIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE BERGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A New York City detective and two friends accused of raping a Burbank woman 
were released Monday after the alleged victim told authorities she had been 
drinking heavily, consented to sex with the police officer and "may have" led 
on his friends. 
</P>
<P>
 "After we interviewed her, we knew no way could we convince 12 jurors beyond a 
doubt" that she was raped, said Deputy Dist. Atty.Walt Lewis, assistant head of 
the district attorney's Pasadena office. 
</P>
<P>
 Lewis added that the 27-year-old woman did not want to pursue charges against 
the three tourists, whom she had accused of raping her after driving her home 
from a local nightclub. 
</P>
<P>
 Released from the Burbank City Jail were New York Police Detective Thomas John 
Kid, 27; John James Calimano, 27; and Richard Daniel Haime, 28, all of New York 
City. 
</P>
<P>
 They were arrested Thursday as they stood in line at NBC Studios in Burbank 
for a taping of the Jay Leno Show and were held in lieu of $1-million bail on 
charges of rape, forced oral copulation and false imprisonment. LESLIE BERGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
