<TEXT>
<P>
 Semiconductor Book-to-Bill Ratio Rises: The closely watched ratio rose to 1.14 
in April from 1.13 in March, the Semiconductor Industry Assn. said.A 
book-to-bill ratio of 1.14 means that for every $100 worth of products shipped, 
or billed, manufacturers received $114 in new orders, or bookings. The ratio is 
computed by dividing three-month average bookings by three-month average 
billings. April bookings rose 4.6% to $2.89 billion from $2.76 billion in 
March. April billings rose 3.6% to $2.53 billion from $2.44 billion in March. 
Analysts said the ratio came in much better than expected. 
</P>
