<P>
FRESNO AUTO DEALER SUES AMERICAN HONDA MOTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Fresno automobile dealer is alleging that American Honda Motor Co. and its 
chief executive officer engaged in fraudulent activity in connection with 
awarding Honda dealerships, according to Automotive News, a trade publication. 
</P>
<P>
 The suit alleges that Koichi Amemiya, American Honda's president and CEO, knew 
about widespread fraud and dealer racketeering in the awarding of Honda and 
Acura dealerships in the past two decades.About 18 similar suits have been 
filed around the country, according to Automotive News. 
</P>
<P>
 The suit was filed about a month after federal officials indicted 13 former 
Honda executives in connection with a fraud and racketeering investigation. 
Eight of the executives subsequently pleaded guilty to fraud-related charges. 
The civil suit filed in U.S. District Court in Santa Clara, contends that top 
Honda executives, including Amemiya, knew about the alleged wrongdoing. 
</P>
